    • Class jwebminer2.gui.OptionsPanel extends javax.swing.JPanel implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • use_yahoo_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox use_yahoo_checkbox
          Whether or not to access the Yahoo! web services.

        • use_google_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox use_google_checkbox
          Whether or not to access the Google web services.

        • google_license_field

          javax.swing.JTextField google_license_field
          The Google License needed to access Google's SOAP web services.

        • use_lastfm_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox use_lastfm_checkbox
          Whether or not to access the Last.FM web services.

        • lastfm_license_field

          javax.swing.JTextField lastfm_license_field
          The license needed to access Last.FM's web services.

        • literal_search_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox literal_search_checkbox
          Whether the query strings are to be searched literally. If so, all words must occur exactly as they appear and in the same order as specified to result in a hit. This is also sometimes known as an exact search or a phrase search.

        • any_not_all_search_strings_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox any_not_all_search_strings_checkbox
          Whether the query strings are searched based on a boolean OR or AND. In the OR case, hits will occur if some but not all of the search words are present and in the AND case hits will only occur if all search words are present.

        • include_hits_with_similar_search_strings_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox include_hits_with_similar_search_strings_checkbox
          Whether hits may be included that do not contain one or more of the specified search string(s) but do contain terms very similar to them (e.g. alternative spellings).

        • suppress_similar_hits_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox suppress_similar_hits_checkbox
          Whether to suppress similar hits, namely ones with identical titles and descriptions or multiple hits from the same host.

        • suppress_adult_content_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox suppress_adult_content_checkbox
          Whether to suppress hits that are classified as adult by the search service.

        • limit_to_language_combobox

          javax.swing.JComboBox<E> limit_to_language_combobox
          Exclude hits that to not belong to the specified language. An entry of "No Limitations" places no language-based restrictions.

        • limit_to_country_combobox

          javax.swing.JComboBox<E> limit_to_country_combobox
          Exclude hits that are not located in the specified country. An entry of "No Limitations" places no location-based restrictions.

        • searching_from_region_combobox

          javax.swing.JComboBox<E> searching_from_region_combobox
          Perform the search using services located in the specified country, if possible (i.e. where the search service is located). Results are not limited to this country.An entry of "No Limitations" causes the default service to be used.

        • limit_to_file_type_combobox

          javax.swing.JComboBox<E> limit_to_file_type_combobox
          Only search for files of the specified type (extension). An entry of "No Limitations" places no file type-based restrictions.

        • normalize_across_web_services_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox normalize_across_web_services_checkbox
          Whether the hits from web services should be normalized before the final feature scores are calculated. This ensures that services that produce fewer hits overall are not underweighted in the final scores.

        • normalize_across_web_sites_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox normalize_across_web_sites_checkbox
          Whether the hits from different web services should be normalized before the final feature scores are calculated. This ensures that sites that produce fewer hits overall are not underweighted in the final scores. This is separate and in addition to the manual weights that can be imposed on the Site* Weightings panel.

        • normalize_scores_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox normalize_scores_checkbox
          Whether final feature scores should be normalized when reported and saved.

        • normalize_scores_by_row_instead_of_overall_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox normalize_scores_by_row_instead_of_overall_checkbox
          Whether final feature scores should be normalized when reported and saved by row rather than overall (if normalize_scores_checkbox is selected).

        • cooccurrence_function_1_button

          javax.swing.JRadioButton cooccurrence_function_1_button
          The scoring function S(a1,a2) = PC(a1,a2) / (1 + (SUMcfromAcnota1(PC(a1,c)) x SUMdfromAdnota2(PC(d,a2)))).

        • cooccurrence_function_2_button

          javax.swing.JRadioButton cooccurrence_function_2_button
          The scoring function S(a1,a2, c) = (PC(a1,a2) / PC(a2)) * (1 - (|PC(a1) - PC(a2)| / PC(c))) where c is the greatest PC(A).

        • cross_tab_function_1_button

          javax.swing.JRadioButton cross_tab_function_1_button
          The scoring function S(a,b) = PC(a,b) / PC(a).

        • cross_tab_function_2_button

          javax.swing.JRadioButton cross_tab_function_2_button
          The scoring function S(a,b) = PC(a,b) / PC(b).

        • cross_tab_function_3_button

          javax.swing.JRadioButton cross_tab_function_3_button
          The scoring function S(a,b) = PC(a,b) / (1 + SUMcfromA(PC(c,b))).

        • cross_tab_function_4_button

          javax.swing.JRadioButton cross_tab_function_4_button
          The scoring function S(a,b) = PC(a,b) / (1 + SUMcfromB(PC(a,c))).

        • display_feature_scores_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox display_feature_scores_checkbox
          Whether or not to display the final scores that will be saved as features in the Results Panel after processing is complete.

        • display_combined_processed_counts_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox display_combined_processed_counts_checkbox
          Whether or not to display the combined (added) processed hit counts for all web services and sites in the Results Panel after processing is complete. This does include site weighting and/or web service normalization, depending on user settings.

        • display_combined_raw_counts_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox display_combined_raw_counts_checkbox
          Whether or not to display the combined (added) raw hit counts for all web services and sites in the Results Panel after processing is complete. This does not include site weighting or web service normalization.

        • display_individual_raw_counts_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox display_individual_raw_counts_checkbox
          Whether or not to display the raw hit counts for each web service and (pre-weighted) network site in the Results Panel after processing is complete.

        • display_queries_used_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox display_queries_used_checkbox
          Whether or not to display the queries actually sent to the web services in the Results Panel after processing is complete. Note that these queries will not include information that was stored in the actual web service objects themselves.

        • display_search_settings_used_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox display_search_settings_used_checkbox
          Whether or not to display the details of all of the settings used to perform searches in the Results Panel after processing is complete.

        • required_filter_words_panel

        • excluded_filter_words_panel

          Allows the user to set words that may not be present on a site in order for it to be counted as a hit.

        • site_weightings_panel

          StringEntryPanel site_weightings_panel
          Allows the user to set the sites to extract features from and to vary the weights assigned to each.

        • options_panel

          OptionsPanel options_panel
          Allows the user to set feature extraction preferences.

        • results_panel

          Shows the results of the last feature extraction.
